.TH TIFF2ICNS 1 "August 28, 2002" "Apple Computer, Inc."
.SH NAME
\fBtiff2icns\fR \- converts TIFF to icns format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tiff2icns
[\fB-noLarge\fR] \fIinfile\fR [\fIoutfile\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tiff2icns
can be used to convert TIFF images to `icns' files used by Icon Services.
.PP
Searches for 48, 32, 16, 128, 256, 512, and 1024 wide images (in that
order) and converts them to icons. Does not do any scaling and does not
generate mini (12x12) icons. If no 32x32 image is found and the
\fB-noLarge\fR flag is not passed, one is generated by scaling the image.
.PP
If no output file is specified, output is written to a file whose name is
the input file name, with the original extension replaced by `.icns'.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-noLarge
\fBtiff2icns\fR always creates a large 32x32 icon unless the
\fB-noLarge\fR flag is passed.
